Key Match Events: The Sacramento Kings defeated the Phoenix Suns with a score of 127-104.
Domantas Sabonis made a three-point basket during the second quarter.
Sacramento Kings shot 15-of-28 (53.6 percent) from beyond the arc.
The Kings also shot 70 percent on their two-point attempts.
The Kings had 38 assists on their 50 made field goals, a season-high for the team.
